      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Class War Gore Could Lose,'' by David Lebedoff (Op-Ed, Aug. 27):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Class War Gore Could Lose,'' by David Lebedoff (Op-Ed, Aug. 27):</p>
        <p>Mr. Lebedoff's argument against the ''meritocracy'' must be tongue-in-cheek.</p>
        <p>Does he really mean to suggest that a presidential candidate (Al Gore) who talks about the importance of education; understands and can explain the facts relevant to domestic and foreign-policy issues and who reads and writes serious books is running at a liability for leading this country because of these actions?</p>
        <p>SUZANNE DICKIE  Chicago, Aug. 27, 2000</p>
      </block>
